title: U.S. wins 1st worlds in 92 years, honors Gaudreau
description: Buffalo Sabres forward Tage Thompson scored 2:02 into overtime, and Team USA outlasted Switzerland 1-0 in the final of the ice hockey world championship Sunday, the first American title in this tournament in 92 years after bringing it home back in 1933.

title: Villa make refereeing complaint after missing out on Champions League
description: Aston Villa have made an official complaint after a "big mistake" by referee Thomas Bramall during a 2-0 loss at Manchester United.

title: 'Big Four' reunite at Nadal's French Open farewell
description: Rafael Nadal reunites with Roger Federer, Novak Djokovic and Andy Murray in a special farewell ceremony to the 14-time French Open champion.

title: Yankees withstand rain delay, late Rockies rally to take rubber match
description: Up 4-2 in the fifth inning, the New York Yankees and Colorado Rockies paused for a rain delay at Coors Field that lasted one hour and 46 minutes. Villa make official complaint to PGMOL after referee howler costs them CL
description: Aston Villa have made an official complaint to the PGMOL over the selection of referee Thomas Bramall for their Premier League final-day match against Man Utd, which Champions League-chasing Villa lost after having a goal controversially ruled out.

title: Liverpool finally lift the Premier League in front of jubilant Anfield
description: Liverpool's players were finally able to lift the Premier League trophy in front of their supporters at Anfield on the final day of the season, the first time that has happened since 1990 and as expected, there were joyous scenes.
